WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.920
This series is crafted for the purpose of entertainment.
All characters, behaviours, settings, and events depicted in this drama are entirely fictitious.
They are not designed to allude to any particular entity, occupation, or group of people.
Viewer discretion is advised.

00:00:10.640 --> 00:00:12.680
[Previously]
Khun Phra Nai had this white house built…

00:00:12.680 --> 00:00:14.880
in hopes of living with his lover here.

00:00:15.160 --> 00:00:16.720
You finally came back to me.

00:00:17.400 --> 00:00:18.680
My dear Chuichai.

00:00:19.360 --> 00:00:23.040
I feel strangely familiar with this place, Mum.

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:25.280
As if it were a home I had left for so long.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:28.600
We used to have a great time here together in the past.

00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:30.760
I thought I’d never get to see you today.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:31.760
Where have you been?

00:00:31.760 --> 00:00:32.920
I went to Kaew’s house.

00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:35.640
That’s her best friend. His name is Kaewta.

00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:38.920
You’ve finally returned.

00:00:39.320 --> 00:00:40.880
Try to make merits whenever you can.

00:00:41.200 --> 00:00:45.160
When the time is right, you’ll finally see that person you wish to see.

00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:46.440
Hey!

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:48.640
You!

00:00:51.920 --> 00:00:52.720
Hey!

00:00:52.720 --> 00:00:59.320
[2490 B.E.]

00:01:04.599 --> 00:01:06.000
You can see me, dear?

00:01:46.920 --> 00:01:48.200
No, you can’t.

00:01:54.240 --> 00:01:55.560
Where did he go?

00:02:09.080 --> 00:02:14.240
When the time comes, you will finally see me.

00:02:33.640 --> 00:02:40.280
♫ Let my thought of you drifted along the wind ♫

00:02:40.280 --> 00:02:49.400
♫ Carrying with it my love to the very far-end ♫

00:02:49.400 --> 00:02:55.480
♫With faint smell of flowers in the air ♫

00:02:56.200 --> 00:03:04.400
♫ Hoping it’d reach that person waiting on the other side ♫

00:03:04.400 --> 00:03:10.800
♫ Sending my love through the air ♫

00:03:11.240 --> 00:03:19.640
♫ I miss you so much more than you can imagine ♫

00:03:19.640 --> 00:03:26.360
♫ Just want you know I don’t want anything ♫

00:03:26.360 --> 00:03:36.280
♫ You don’t have to return the feelings if you don’t want to ♫

00:03:54.360 --> 00:04:01.200
♫ May the wind carry this song…♫

00:04:01.880 --> 00:04:09.200
♫…in my heart to you ♫

00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:17.560
♫ No matter for how long, I’ll always love you ♫

00:04:17.560 --> 00:04:22.640
♫ I’ll love you…until the time is through ♫

00:04:22.640 --> 00:04:29.480
[Interminable]
♫ I’ll love you…until the time is through ♫

00:04:47.159 --> 00:04:48.560
Kaew!

00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:50.760
Mum.

00:04:50.760 --> 00:04:52.120
Are you done giving alms to the monks?

00:04:53.080 --> 00:04:53.880
Yes, Mum.

00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:59.000
I also dedicated merits to Khun Phra Nai, the owner of this house,

00:04:59.520 --> 00:05:02.200
and to all the spirits here too.

00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:06.680
Amen.

00:05:11.640 --> 00:05:13.600
Let us also rejoice in your merit…

00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:17.880
and be thankful to you on behalf of all the spirits here.

00:05:17.880 --> 00:05:18.640
Yes.

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:21.920
Amen.

00:05:25.520 --> 00:05:26.880
That’s right, Mum.

00:05:27.560 --> 00:05:32.080
Have you seen anyone walking this way earlier?

00:05:33.520 --> 00:05:34.440
Who is it?

00:05:36.240 --> 00:05:37.720
I don’t know too.

00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:42.000
He’s a man in a white suit.

00:05:44.480 --> 00:05:45.440
I didn’t see anyone.

00:05:48.120 --> 00:05:52.320
That’s strange. I was walking right after him but then he suddenly disappeared.

00:06:06.200 --> 00:06:09.120
I’ll go get you something to eat then, okay?

00:06:09.720 --> 00:06:10.520
Yes.

00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:34.640
[2455 B.E.]

00:07:34.640 --> 00:07:35.600
Saen.

00:07:36.240 --> 00:07:39.000
Are you sure this is where my dear Chuichai lives?

00:07:39.200 --> 00:07:43.440
Aww, is she “your dear Chuichai” now, my lord?

00:07:45.400 --> 00:07:46.600
Of course, I am sure.

00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:50.040
I already asked the servants at *Luang Sanor’s house. (*Head of Classical Thai Orchestra Bureau)

00:07:50.040 --> 00:07:52.680
They said the lady who performed the Chuichai dance that day…

00:07:52.680 --> 00:07:54.520
Her name is Payom.

00:08:01.560 --> 00:08:03.080
Is anybody home?

00:08:12.040 --> 00:08:13.240
Who are you here for?

00:08:13.440 --> 00:08:15.040
My name is Saen, Miss.

00:08:15.160 --> 00:08:17.680
And this is my brother, Khun Yai.

00:08:17.960 --> 00:08:18.880
Hello, Miss.

00:08:19.240 --> 00:08:19.960
Yes.

00:08:22.560 --> 00:08:25.200
Why are you here then?

00:08:26.680 --> 00:08:29.840
We’re looking for Lady Chuichai who performed the dance at the party…

00:08:29.840 --> 00:08:32.799
at His Royal Highness Prince’s palace the other day.

00:08:33.360 --> 00:08:35.120
The one called Payom, Miss.

00:08:35.640 --> 00:08:39.080
Oh, I’m afraid that’s me then.

00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:48.040
Your name is Payom?

00:08:49.400 --> 00:08:54.320
So? Why do you want to see me?

00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:03.480
Those servants at Luang Sanor really told me it’s Payom.

00:09:03.880 --> 00:09:07.840
How reckless. We could’ve been killed if that were a thief’s lair.

00:09:08.320 --> 00:09:11.240
Then we should just arrest them and send them to the police.

00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:14.880
Thief! Catch him!

00:09:15.760 --> 00:09:17.320
There’s a thief, Khun Yai.

00:09:19.480 --> 00:09:21.600
Move! Out of the way!

00:09:26.120 --> 00:09:27.120
Hey! Stop!

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:47.400
Only within an arm reach but feels so far away.

00:09:49.080 --> 00:09:51.080
Although he can’t see you yet,

00:09:51.400 --> 00:09:54.120
his heart still remembers you, Khun Yai.

00:09:54.960 --> 00:09:59.000
But when, Saen? When will Kaew notice me?

00:10:03.120 --> 00:10:04.720
That day will certainly come.

00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:06.840
Do you still remember what the Abbot said?

00:10:16.120 --> 00:10:17.920
Souls that are bonded…

00:10:18.880 --> 00:10:21.400
cannot stay parted forever.

00:10:28.640 --> 00:10:31.880
That’s right but…

00:10:33.280 --> 00:10:35.240
Everything happens in its own time.

00:10:39.240 --> 00:10:44.080
When that day comes, I shall never let him go ever again.

00:10:47.280 --> 00:10:49.320
May that day arrive soon.

00:11:14.280 --> 00:11:15.600
Kaewta.

00:11:21.080 --> 00:11:23.160
That’s Ruedee’s best friend.

00:11:23.160 --> 00:11:24.520
His name is Kaewta.

00:11:24.640 --> 00:11:26.000
Kaewta?

00:11:29.720 --> 00:11:30.520
Be careful, dear.

00:11:31.640 --> 00:11:32.400
Sister.

00:11:32.400 --> 00:11:34.080
Does it hurt a lot, dear?

00:11:34.920 --> 00:11:36.200
Kaewta!

00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:40.720
Why was I so furious?

00:11:44.280 --> 00:11:45.840
Miss Sophee.

00:11:46.200 --> 00:11:49.360
Miss Nid and Miss Ruedee are here to see you. Would you like them to come up now?

00:11:50.720 --> 00:11:51.760
Let them in.

00:11:52.080 --> 00:11:52.880
Yes, ma’am.

00:11:54.960 --> 00:11:56.200
Hello, Aunt Nid.

00:11:59.160 --> 00:12:00.640
Hello, Sister.

00:12:04.680 --> 00:12:09.120
I heard you have a fever, so I’m a bit worried.

00:12:09.520 --> 00:12:12.080
How are you feeling, dear?

00:12:13.040 --> 00:12:15.520
Much better now. A few more days and I’ll be as good as new.

00:12:15.520 --> 00:12:17.520
Thank you so much for your concern, Aunty.

00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:19.680
You shouldn’t have troubled yourself coming all the way here.

00:12:21.480 --> 00:12:26.360
My mother would like to invite you to my brother’s welcome back party.

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:30.160
Is he returning from abroad soon?

00:12:31.360 --> 00:12:32.160
Yes.

00:12:34.200 --> 00:12:37.000
How wonderful. I’d absolutely be there.

00:12:37.320 --> 00:12:39.880
I also have something for you.

00:12:42.000 --> 00:12:43.120
What is it?

00:12:50.920 --> 00:12:52.160
Here, take it.

00:13:13.840 --> 00:13:15.040
This hairpin…

00:13:16.960 --> 00:13:20.840
is an inheritance from my cousin Sophee.

00:13:26.640 --> 00:13:28.200
It looks so familiar.

00:13:34.640 --> 00:13:39.880
Sophee, I think this pin belongs to you, dear.

00:13:41.400 --> 00:13:42.640
Is it for me?

00:13:44.160 --> 00:13:49.040
Yes, think of it as a gift to welcome you back.

00:14:07.920 --> 00:14:10.800
[2455 B.E.]

00:14:11.080 --> 00:14:13.240
Can you please put it on for me?

00:14:14.440 --> 00:14:16.760
Of course. Come.

00:14:28.360 --> 00:14:29.640
Thank you.

00:14:30.200 --> 00:14:32.840
You look beautiful with this hairpin on you.

00:14:41.560 --> 00:14:44.000
Shall the next life truly exist…

00:14:45.440 --> 00:14:55.200
I solemnly vow to remember this love and pain…

00:15:01.320 --> 00:15:03.640
and shall get back at all of them!

00:15:18.320 --> 00:15:19.800
What’s wrong, dear?

00:15:20.080 --> 00:15:24.240
Sister, are you all right? Sister!

00:15:50.520 --> 00:15:53.240
- Sophee!
- Anyone, fetch me an inhaler!

00:15:53.240 --> 00:15:54.960
Sophee just fainted. Quickly!

00:15:54.960 --> 00:15:57.040
An inhaler!

00:16:06.040 --> 00:16:08.360
The moment she touched that hairpin,

00:16:08.640 --> 00:16:13.800
she screamed so loud and fainted right in front of me and my mother.

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:16.360
Was it that bad?

00:16:17.600 --> 00:16:22.520
Kaew, I think there’s a ghost trapped in that pin.

00:16:23.400 --> 00:16:25.080
Nonsense, Ruedee.

00:16:25.480 --> 00:16:28.520
What kind of ghost will live in such a tiny pin like that?

00:16:30.520 --> 00:16:34.640
You didn’t see what she was like after she became conscious.

00:16:35.640 --> 00:16:36.440
Why?

00:16:37.640 --> 00:16:39.920
It was very strange and also…

00:16:40.760 --> 00:16:42.440
very scary.

00:16:45.960 --> 00:16:48.760
Mother, she already came to.

00:16:49.560 --> 00:16:50.360
Sister.

00:16:54.320 --> 00:16:55.400
Sister.

00:17:02.360 --> 00:17:03.400
Nid.

00:17:04.680 --> 00:17:05.480
Yes.

00:17:09.160 --> 00:17:11.680
How are you feeling, Sister?

00:17:12.040 --> 00:17:13.160
I’m fine!

00:17:13.680 --> 00:17:18.720
Are you sure, dear? You screamed so loud everyone here got frightened.

00:17:18.720 --> 00:17:20.200
Then you fainted.

00:17:20.200 --> 00:17:21.800
It was just a bad dream.

00:17:27.280 --> 00:17:29.480
When she looked at me,

00:17:30.480 --> 00:17:33.440
I felt so creepy and had goosebumps all over.

00:17:34.440 --> 00:17:38.640
You know how I usually don’t like her and am quite scared of her.

00:17:39.560 --> 00:17:43.600
But now, it’s even worse.

00:17:44.320 --> 00:17:51.280
As if I might be dead if I spent just a minute longer in her presence.

00:17:53.360 --> 00:17:55.400
You’re overthinking, Ruedee.

00:17:56.120 --> 00:17:57.800
She’s your sister somehow.

00:17:59.800 --> 00:18:05.280
She might be just a cousin, but you two are still related so I don't think she'd hurt you.

00:18:05.800 --> 00:18:09.440
I don’t know. But I’m scared.

00:18:17.560 --> 00:18:18.840
Sophee.

00:18:54.080 --> 00:18:59.840
This pin is proof that I was the first one he loved.

00:19:00.920 --> 00:19:03.760
You look beautiful with this hairpin on you.

00:19:04.240 --> 00:19:07.920
I still remember how you used to practise making garlands for the monks.

00:19:07.920 --> 00:19:11.120
She grew up so quickly, Father.

00:19:12.240 --> 00:19:15.400
Thank you, Yai. You were on a business trip…

00:19:15.400 --> 00:19:18.440
but still didn’t forget to buy me and your sister gifts.

00:19:19.400 --> 00:19:23.080
Next time, just buy it for her only.

00:19:24.720 --> 00:19:25.760
How could I?

00:19:26.080 --> 00:19:28.600
Since my parents passed away,

00:19:28.600 --> 00:19:30.880
you have always taken good care of me, Father.

00:19:31.400 --> 00:19:33.640
These gifts are indeed nothing…

00:19:33.640 --> 00:19:36.120
compared to your kindness in caring and raising me up.

00:20:06.760 --> 00:20:09.280
No matter how far…

00:20:10.720 --> 00:20:12.720
or how many lives I must live,

00:20:15.480 --> 00:20:17.760
I will find you, my love.

00:20:38.640 --> 00:20:39.960
Kaewta!

00:20:56.560 --> 00:20:58.040
Why are you dressed up today?

00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:09.280
What’s with being so meticulous?

00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:16.000
Kaewta!

00:21:16.160 --> 00:21:16.960
Kaewta!

00:21:18.400 --> 00:21:19.640
Kaew.

00:21:20.720 --> 00:21:22.120
Mum.

00:21:23.800 --> 00:21:25.040
Are you leaving, dear?

00:21:25.320 --> 00:21:28.560
Yes, I’ll probably be home late tonight.

00:21:29.000 --> 00:21:32.880
But don’t worry, Ruedee has promised to drop me off.

00:21:34.080 --> 00:21:35.480
Just take care of yourself.

00:21:36.560 --> 00:21:38.600
Yes. I’m going then.

00:21:39.640 --> 00:21:41.360
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

00:21:46.080 --> 00:21:47.320
Why would he be home late?

00:21:51.800 --> 00:21:53.800
Why do you have to come home late?

00:21:54.120 --> 00:21:55.160
I’m worried.

00:21:57.200 --> 00:22:00.600
Where are you going, Kaewta?

00:22:02.200 --> 00:22:04.320
Kaewta, I’m talking to you!

00:22:06.360 --> 00:22:07.040
Kaew!

00:22:10.080 --> 00:22:12.360
Kaewta, are you all right?

00:22:14.040 --> 00:22:15.360
Sin! Saen!

00:22:16.640 --> 00:22:17.400
Come help Kaew!

00:22:17.400 --> 00:22:18.120
Khun Kaew!

00:22:18.120 --> 00:22:18.920
Khun Kaew!

00:22:19.240 --> 00:22:20.040
What happened?

00:22:20.080 --> 00:22:21.160
Are you all right?

00:22:21.240 --> 00:22:22.280
I just tripped.

00:22:22.760 --> 00:22:23.880
Sin, go get the first-aid kit.

00:22:24.560 --> 00:22:25.360
Go!

00:22:25.400 --> 00:22:27.760
Please be careful. Can you get up?

00:22:28.400 --> 00:22:29.280
Yes.

00:22:34.440 --> 00:22:36.800
I’m okay, Saen.

00:22:40.520 --> 00:22:43.120
Is watching you like this the only thing I can do?

00:22:47.560 --> 00:22:49.120
Do you think you can walk?

00:22:50.160 --> 00:22:51.160
Yes.

00:22:53.000 --> 00:22:54.560
At least it’s not so swollen.

00:22:57.640 --> 00:22:59.640
But you still have to be careful though.

00:23:00.520 --> 00:23:01.160
Saen!

00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:03.280
Yes?

00:23:08.200 --> 00:23:09.360
Can you see it?

00:23:10.120 --> 00:23:11.280
See what?

00:23:13.720 --> 00:23:15.560
I can come out of the white house now.

00:23:16.640 --> 00:23:17.960
You’re right, Khun Yai!

00:23:19.320 --> 00:23:20.240
Saen,

00:23:22.040 --> 00:23:23.560
who are you talking to?

00:23:25.760 --> 00:23:28.120
Sin! Did you find it?

00:23:28.800 --> 00:23:29.960
Yes, coming!

00:23:30.440 --> 00:23:31.320
Hurry up.

00:23:34.360 --> 00:23:35.520
Here you go.

00:23:36.160 --> 00:23:37.240
Go tend the wound for him.

00:23:37.880 --> 00:23:38.920
Where is it, Khun Kaew?

00:23:43.240 --> 00:23:47.440
It might be because of Kaew or…

00:23:48.800 --> 00:23:54.520
perhaps it’s not the white house that traps me inside…

00:23:57.360 --> 00:23:59.080
but rather my own heart.

00:23:59.360 --> 00:24:03.120
I’m trapped inside my own heart only to wait for him.

00:24:08.520 --> 00:24:10.200
It’s about time, Khun Yai.

00:24:10.760 --> 00:24:14.280
It’s time for your spirit to become free from such interminable wait.

00:24:23.240 --> 00:24:25.440
There you go. You should be fine soon.

00:24:26.240 --> 00:24:27.760
Go get the car then.

00:24:27.760 --> 00:24:28.520
To drop Khun Kaew off.

00:24:28.600 --> 00:24:29.560
Okay.

00:24:33.760 --> 00:24:35.920
Please wait for Sin to get the car first.

00:24:50.120 --> 00:24:51.960
It’s really nothing at all.

00:25:07.720 --> 00:25:09.120
It’s good that you’re fine.

00:25:15.920 --> 00:25:20.200
Listen, why do you have to dress up so meticulously for someone else’s party?

00:25:20.200 --> 00:25:22.360
You’re only a guest, not the host.

00:25:35.200 --> 00:25:36.760
Here you go, Khun Kaew.

00:25:37.200 --> 00:25:38.240
Thank you, Sin.

00:25:38.400 --> 00:25:39.200
My pleasure.

00:25:40.640 --> 00:25:41.440
Sin.

00:25:45.120 --> 00:25:47.840
Why? Are you getting possessive?

00:25:49.800 --> 00:25:51.800
I was just stating the fact.

00:25:53.840 --> 00:25:55.960
Oh, right.

00:26:01.120 --> 00:26:02.680
Who are you talking to?

00:26:03.120 --> 00:26:05.320
No one. I wasn’t talking to anyone.

00:26:07.920 --> 00:26:09.640
See? There’s no one else here.

00:26:11.880 --> 00:26:14.640
I think we’d better hurry or we might be late.

00:26:16.360 --> 00:26:17.520
Please.

00:26:23.320 --> 00:26:27.440
Wow, are you really not possessive?

00:26:30.000 --> 00:26:31.560
Are you talking to me?

00:26:32.880 --> 00:26:35.440
Of course, I’m talking to you.

00:26:35.840 --> 00:26:39.560
I mean if you’re going to attend someone else’s party,

00:26:40.000 --> 00:26:43.440
it’s important to be very meticulous in what you’ll be wearing…

00:26:43.720 --> 00:26:45.200
in order to show respect to the host.

00:26:47.080 --> 00:26:49.320
Is what I’m wearing meticulous?

00:26:50.160 --> 00:26:51.120
Very much.

00:26:51.480 --> 00:26:52.440
- Sin.
- Yes?

00:26:52.760 --> 00:26:54.160
Shut up and drive!!

00:26:54.440 --> 00:26:57.680
Yes, sir. Let’s get going, Khun Kaew.

00:27:05.800 --> 00:27:07.520
Hello, Uncle and Aunty.

00:27:09.440 --> 00:27:14.760
Do you know Ruedee has been waiting for you all morning?

00:27:15.160 --> 00:27:17.680
She’s afraid her bestie might bail on her.

00:27:19.000 --> 00:27:20.520
Why would I do that?

00:27:21.120 --> 00:27:22.960
A promise is a promise.

00:27:24.360 --> 00:27:25.600
That’s right, my bestie.

00:27:32.280 --> 00:27:33.120
Sin.

00:27:33.120 --> 00:27:33.640
Yes?

00:27:33.760 --> 00:27:34.880
Thank you for dropping me off.

00:27:34.960 --> 00:27:36.000
You’re welcome.

00:27:36.200 --> 00:27:37.920
You can go back first.

00:27:38.520 --> 00:27:39.880
I can go home myself.

00:27:40.040 --> 00:27:41.920
You can’t do that. My da…

00:27:44.240 --> 00:27:48.520
I mean, Saen, he has ordered me to wait for you and take you home after the party.

00:27:49.240 --> 00:27:50.240
But…

00:27:50.600 --> 00:27:53.320
It’s all right, Khun Kaew. I can wait.

00:27:53.440 --> 00:27:54.840
It’s fine, Kaew.

00:27:54.840 --> 00:27:58.280
If Sin wants to wait, then let him.

00:27:58.760 --> 00:28:02.280
